emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think it really depends on where the Radiation is coming from to cause aurorae. Does Olu\u0027um emit radiation (according to the lore) because if so aurorae might look\u00A0good on sheathe. (sorry for the late reply, had to go to bed)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso one more thing regarding Scorch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes it have a powerful magnetic field?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gameslinx","CreatedById":144828,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-26T15:10:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222997856\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155740\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490540811\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173044\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ModerndayLink64\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, ModerndayLink64 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think it really depends on where the Radiation is coming from to cause aurorae. Does Olu\u0027um emit radiation (according to the lore) because if so aurorae might look\u00A0good on sheathe. (sorry for the late reply, had to go to bed)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom jupiter: \u0022Jupiter\u0027s magnetic field is l\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003Earger, complex and up to ten times the strength of Earth\u0027s.\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cb style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003EJupiter\u0027s magnetic field\u003C/b\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Eis thought to arise from electrical currents emanating from a rapidly spinning, metallic hydrogen interior\u0022\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003EAnd so the same applies to Olu\u0027um. It\u0027s hot enough and the giant spins, therefore the core must also spin, creating a magnetic field \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShort answer = yes, even though I never clarified what Olu\u0027um\u0027s core was made of!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ModerndayLink","CreatedById":173044,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-26T15:16:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222997865\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155740\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490541049\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144828\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gameslinx\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, Gameslinx said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom jupiter: \u0022Jupiter\u0027s magnetic field is l\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003Earger, complex and up to ten times the strength of Earth\u0027s.\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cb style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003EJupiter\u0027s magnetic field\u003C/b\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Eis thought to arise from electrical currents emanating from a rapidly spinning, metallic hydrogen interior\u0022\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#222222;\u0022\u003EAnd so the same applies to Olu\u0027um. It\u0027s hot enough and the giant spins, therefore the core must also spin, creating a magnetic field \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShort answer = yes, even though I never clarified what Olu\u0027um\u0027s core was made of!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwell than in that case I don\u0027t see why Sheathe would not have aurorae\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso\u00A0Is olu\u0027um supposed to have a very violent atmosphere?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-26T15:18:49Z\u0022 title=\u002203/26/2017 03:18  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 26, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by ModerndayLink64\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gameslinx","CreatedById":144828,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-26T15:26:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222997876\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155740\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490541413\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173044\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ModerndayLink64\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, ModerndayLink64 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwell than in that case I don\u0027t see why Sheathe would not have aurorae\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso\u00A0Is olu\u0027um supposed to have a very violent atmosphere?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause it\u0027s a sub-star (hot Jupiter, if you like), the closer you get to the top layer of the atmosphere, the hotter it becomes, because the heat from the giant is mixed with the heat reflected from the sun by the atmosphere. Below the top layer, the giant actually gets cooler until around 10% of the way down where it heats up again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom this you could imagine Olu\u0027um has a violent atmosphere, because heat creates convection currents and high winds. You could argue the atmosphere isn\u0027t as violent because the temperature is generally equal even on the day-night sides. This is because the top layer reflects the sun much more than a regular atmosphere, so the temperature is uniform further down.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn short, I think the atmosphere definitely turns 1 in one definitive direction, and that would help with the magnetic field. (Plus auroras look nice \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"flack","CreatedById":172991,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-26T15:41:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlaying around with your awsome mod and Kerbalism radiations!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat work btw!\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther ipsEmbeddedOther_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=http://imgur.com/a/YAfiC\u0022 style=\u0022height:465px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ModerndayLink","CreatedById":173044,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-26T15:46:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222997892\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155740\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490541980\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144828\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gameslinx\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 minutes ago, Gameslinx said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause it\u0027s a sub-star (hot Jupiter, if you like), the closer you get to the top layer of the atmosphere, the hotter it becomes, because the heat from the giant is mixed with the heat reflected from the sun by the atmosphere. Below the top layer, the giant actually gets cooler until around 10% of the way down where it heats up again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom this you could imagine Olu\u0027um has a violent atmosphere, because heat creates convection currents and high winds. You could argue the atmosphere isn\u0027t as violent because the temperature is generally equal even on the day-night sides. This is because the top layer reflects the sun much more than a regular atmosphere, so the temperature is uniform further down.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn short, I think the atmosphere definitely turns 1 in one definitive direction, and that would help with the magnetic field. (Plus auroras look nice \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it hot enough to emit small amounts of light on the night side?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder if that is possible...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-26T15:46:49Z\u0022 title=\u002203/26/2017 03:46  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 26, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by ModerndayLink64\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gameslinx","CreatedById":144828,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-26T15:49:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222997905\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155740\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490542875\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022172991\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022flack\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, flack said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlaying around with your awsome mod and Kerbalism radiations!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat work btw!\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther ipsEmbeddedOther_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=http://imgur.com/a/YAfiC\u0022 style=\u0022height:495px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhoa! As well as looking awesome, that helps me quite a lot!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the images I can see that Telos slips inside its magnetosphere for about a third of its orbit (or so). Perhaps this explains why Telos\u0027 atmosphere is so thin even though its quite heavy - being outside the magnetosphere/magnetic field means that it loses all its protection and its atmosphere is exposed to\u00A0Kerbol\u0027s solar wind? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:o\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon2.png\u0022 title=\u0022:o\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The White Guardian","CreatedById":148627,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-26T15:50:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222997332\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155740\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490484052\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144828\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gameslinx\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 hours ago, Gameslinx said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI might also add a magnetic field (aurora) around either Sheathe or thelai as there both composed of a metal core.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt might look a little wonky because of a lack of atmosphere, but what do you think? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA aurora is the reaction of an interaction between charged particles and a planet\u0027s atmosphere.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAllow me to explain:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. Charged particles from the Sun aproach Earth.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. Earth\u0027s magnetic field pulls on these charged particles and pulls them to the poles.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3. The charged particles smash into the atmosphere, resulting in a lightshow known as an aurora.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo rocky planets technically can\u0027t have aurora\u0027s. But hey, this is KSP, so if you want to, then why not? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gameslinx","CreatedById":144828,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-26T15:53:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222997921\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155740\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490543402\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022148627\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The White Guardian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, The White Guardian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA aurora is the reaction of an interaction between charged particles and a planet\u0027s atmosphere.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAllow me to explain:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. Charged particles from the Sun aproach Earth.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. Earth\u0027s magnetic field pulls on these charged particles and pulls them to the poles.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3. The charged particles smash into the atmosphere, resulting in a lightshow known as an aurora.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo rocky planets technically can\u0027t have aurora\u0027s. But hey, this is KSP, so if you want to, then why not? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAhhh I thought the atmosphere came into it somewhere, but a google search returned otherwise. I just searched again and found it\u0027s electrons VS the air that causes it.\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EBut\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003ESheathe\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Etechnically\u00A0\u003C/em\u003Ehas all that dust floating about doesn\u0027t it (Kinda simulated it with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Environmental Visual Enhancement (mod)\u0022\u003EEVE\u003C/abbr\u003E). Nothing overly dense, but hey. I\u0027ll see how an aurora looks on it and decide based on that!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222997914\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155740\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490543182\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173044\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ModerndayLink64\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, ModerndayLink64 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it hot enough to emit small amounts of light on the night side?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis occurs in stars, but won\u0027t work for Olu\u0027um (KSP limitations prevent me from adding a light source to Olu\u0027um because it\u0027s not a star)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo from that, it doesn\u0027t produce light:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/vqt5diM.png\u0022 alt=\u0022vqt5diM.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ModerndayLink","CreatedById":173044,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-26T16:01:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndo you think you could add an \u0022aurora\u0022 that uses a texture\u00A0similar to\u00A0this \u003Ca href=\u0022http://dropcanvas.com/3hrm8/1\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://dropcanvas.com/3hrm8/1\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(because auroras are just glowing cloud layers)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"flack","CreatedById":172991,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-26T16:05:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222997919\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155740\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490543349\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144828\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gameslinx\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, Gameslinx said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhoa! As well as looking awesome, that helps me quite a lot!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the images I can see that Telos slips inside its magnetosphere for about a third of its orbit (or so). Perhaps this explains why Telos\u0027 atmosphere is so thin even though its quite heavy - being outside the magnetosphere/magnetic field means that it loses all its protection and its atmosphere is exposed to\u00A0Kerbol\u0027s solar wind? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:o\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon2.png\u0022 title=\u0022:o\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther ipsEmbeddedOther_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=http://imgur.com/a/Gh7WY\u0022 style=\u0022height:465px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMagnetic fields for the stock planets! You might find this useful!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gameslinx","CreatedById":144828,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-26T16:07:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222997927\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155740\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490544082\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173044\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ModerndayLink64\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, ModerndayLink64 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndo you think you could add an \u0022aurora\u0022 that uses a texture\u00A0similar to\u00A0this \u003Ca href=\u0022http://dropcanvas.com/3hrm8/1\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://dropcanvas.com/3hrm8/1\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(because auroras are just glowing cloud layers)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s unlikely. Kerbol\u0027s radiation isn\u0027t powerful enough to have that much of an effect that far away, especially on a massive gas giant. I tried experimenting with colouring it and it\u0027s a nightmare, but after applying it to Olu\u0027um I think it would leave people slightly confused, sorry \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ModerndayLink","CreatedById":173044,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-26T16:10:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222997937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155740\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221490544432\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144828\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gameslinx\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Gameslinx said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s unlikely. Kerbol\u0027s radiation isn\u0027t powerful enough to have that much of an effect that far away, especially on a massive gas giant. I tried experimenting with colouring it and it\u0027s a nightmare, but after applying it to Olu\u0027um I think it would leave people slightly confused, sorry \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nno problem, I was just curious\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gameslinx","CreatedById":144828,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-26T16:10:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/1d3RXov.png\u0022 alt=\u00221d3RXov.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAdded a veeeery slight aurora to mimic the small amount of dust on Sheathe. It doesn\u0027t look noticeable unrealistic (that\u0027s probably subjective), just a nice feature to notice and, of course,\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EAURORAS!\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ModerndayLink","CreatedById":173044,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-26T16:14:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nlooks nice!\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gameslinx","CreatedById":144828,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-26T16:14:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUpdate: Build going out in around an hour and a half. Any last suggestions/requests? Make em quick or wait till next week \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}